s."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Winslow was born in 1406, in Bourton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 2 sons and 3 daughters with Agnes Throgmorton. He died on 31 March 1463, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1406–31 March 1463":"1406–31. märts 1463","1398–Female":"1398–Surnud","1436–1501":"1436–1501","1439–1534":"1439–1534","1443–1470":"1443–1470","1444–1452":"1444–1452","1444–1513":"1444–1513","1406–1463":"1406–1463","31 March 1463":"31. märts 1463","1470":"1470","1436":"1436","1513":"1513","1534":"1534","1501":"1501","1444":"1444","1443":"1443","1398":"1398","1452":"1452","1463":"1463","1406":"1406","1439":"1439","Begbroke, Oxfordshire, England":"Begbroke, Oxfordshire, England","Bourton, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Bourton, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Burton, Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Buton, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1406–31 March 1463":"1406–31. maaliskuuta 1463","1398–Female":"1398–Kuollut","1436–1501":"1436–1501","1439–1534":"1439–1534","1443–1470":"1443–1470","1444–1452":"1444–1452","1444–1513":"1444–1513","